From: =?UTF-8?q?Witold=20Bo=C5=82t?= <witold.bolt@jit.team>
Date: Fri, 26 Jun 2026 23:10:21 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 13/17] =?UTF-8?q?v3dv:=20drop=20Phoenix=20DISABLE=5FTFU=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?force=20=E2=80=94=20winsys=20now=20implements=20SUBMIT=5FTFU?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The Phoenix no-WSI fb0 winsys (v3d_phoenix_winsys.c) previously handled only
DRM_V3D_SUBMIT_CL and fell through to `default: return 0`, making every
DRM_V3D_SUBMIT_TFU a silent no-op. V3DV uses the TFU for buffer->image /
image->image copies of TILED/OPTIMAL images (all sampled textures), so every
texture upload never executed and the image stayed zero -> every sampled
texture rendered black (#29). We worked around this by forcing
V3D_DEBUG_DISABLE_TFU so copies routed to the CL meta fallback.

ioc_submit_tfu is now implemented in the winsys (programs the V3D 4.2 TFU
registers and waits for TFU-done), so V3DV can use its preferred hardware TFU
copy path. Remove the DISABLE_TFU override.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 src/broadcom/vulkan/v3dv_device.c | 23 ++++++-----------------
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 17 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/broadcom/vulkan/v3dv_device.c b/src/broadcom/vulkan/v3dv_device.c
index 199c9c27123..26a0ce26109 100644
--- a/src/broadcom/vulkan/v3dv_device.c
+++ b/src/broadcom/vulkan/v3dv_device.c
@@ -693,23 +693,12 @@ v3dv_CreateInstance(const VkInstanceCreateInfo *pCreateInfo,
 
    v3d_process_debug_variable();
 
-#if defined(__phoenix__)
-   /* Phoenix no-WSI fb0 winsys does not implement the DRM_V3D_SUBMIT_TFU ioctl (its
-    * ioctl dispatch handles only DRM_V3D_SUBMIT_CL; everything else is a silent no-op
-    * `default: return 0`). The TFU is V3DV's *preferred* (faster) path for buffer<->image
-    * and image<->image copies, blits, and mipmap generation of tiled/OPTIMAL images, so on
-    * this port every such copy was submitted as a TFU job that never executed -> the
-    * destination image stayed at its alloc-time zero -> every sampled texture rendered
-    * BLACK (root-caused: notex draws fine, all textured draws black, descriptors/samplers
-    * valid). Forcing DISABLE_TFU routes ALL of those operations to the CL fallback
-    * (copy_*_tlb / blit_shader), which submits through DRM_V3D_SUBMIT_CL — the path the
-    * winsys does execute. DISABLE_TFU is an upstream-supported debug mode, so a non-TFU CL
-    * fallback is guaranteed for every TFU path. This is correctness (not perf) on this
-    * winsys; implementing the TFU submit is a future optimization.
-    * TODO(vkquake-port): drop once ioc_submit_tfu is implemented in v3d_phoenix_winsys.c. */
-   v3d_mesa_debug |= V3D_DEBUG_DISABLE_TFU;
-   fprintf(stderr, "v3dv: Phoenix DISABLE_TFU forced (no-WSI winsys, CL copy fallback)\n");
-#endif
+   /* Phoenix no-WSI fb0 winsys: the TFU (texture formatting unit) buffer->image / image->image
+    * copy path is now implemented in the winsys (v3d_phoenix_winsys.c ioc_submit_tfu, the
+    * DRM_V3D_SUBMIT_TFU ioctl), so V3DV uses its preferred hardware TFU copy for TILED/OPTIMAL
+    * texture uploads, blits and mipmap generation — no DISABLE_TFU override is needed. (It was
+    * previously forced on because the winsys's ioctl dispatch ended `default: return 0`, making
+    * every TFU job a silent no-op, so every sampled texture rendered black — #29.) */
 
    instance->vk.physical_devices.enumerate = enumerate_devices;
    instance->vk.physical_devices.destroy = destroy_physical_device;
